obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (24655)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24655&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Commission`
  line `for Minorities Act, 1992.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
  line
  line `2. 17th May, 1993, vide notification No. S.O. 317(E), dated 17th May, 1993, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (24656)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Added by Act 41 of 1995, s.2 (w.e.f. 18-9-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24656&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Commission" means the National Commission for Minorities constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Member" means a Member of the Commission ^1`
  line `[and includes the Vice-Chairperson];`
  line
  line `(c) "minority", for the purposes of this Act, means a community notified as such by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (24657)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of the National Commission for Minorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Chairperson and six Members" (w.e.f. 18-9-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24657&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall`
  line `constitute a body to be known as the National Commission for Minorities to exercise the powers`
  line `conferred on, and to perform the functions assigned to, it under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall consist of a ^1`
  line `[Chairperson, a Vice-Chairperson and five Members] to be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government from amongst persons of eminence, ability and integrity:`
  line
  line `Provided that five Members including the Chairperson shall be from amongst the minority`
  line communities.
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (24658)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24658&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson`
  line `and every Member shall hold office for a term of three years from the date he assumes office.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or a Member may, by writing under his hand addressed to the Central`
  line `Government, resign from the office of Chairperson or, as the case may be, of the Member at any time.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall remove a person from the office of Chairperson or a Member`
  line `referred to in sub-section (2) if that person--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(b) is convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence which, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, involves moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `(c) becomes of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(d) refuses to act or becomes incapable of acting;`
  line
  line `(e) is, without obtaining leave of absence from the Commission, absent from three consecutive`
  line `meetings of the Commission; or`
  line
  line `(f) has, in the opinion of the Central Government, so abused the position of Chairperson or`
  line `Member as to render that person's continuance in office detrimental to the interests of minorities or`
  line `the public interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be removed under this clause until that person has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `(4) A vacancy caused under sub-section (2) or otherwise shall be filled by fresh nomination.`
  line
  line `(5) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson and Members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (24659)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Officers and other employees of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24659&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall provide`
  line `the Commission with a Secretary and such other officers and employees as may be necessary for the`
  line `efficient performance of the functions of the Commission under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `officers and other employees appointed for the purpose of the Commission shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (24660)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Salaries and allowances to be paid out of grants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24660&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The salaries and allowances payable to the`
  line `Chairperson and Members and the administrative expenses, including salaries, allowances and pensions`
  line `payable to the officers and other employees referred to in section 5, shall be paid out of the grants referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1) of section 10.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (24661)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24661&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the`
  line `Commission shall be questioned or shall be invalid merely on the ground of the existence of any vacancy`
  line `or defect in the constitution of the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (24662)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Procedure to be regulated by the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24662&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall meet as and when`
  line `necessary at such time and place as the Chairperson may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(3) All orders and decisions of the Commission shall be authenticated by the Secretary or any other`
  line `officer of the Commission duly authorised by the Secretary on this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (24663)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Functions of the Commission .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24663&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1)The Commission shall perform all or any of the following`
  line `functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) evaluate the progress of the development of minorities under the Union and States;`
  line
  line `(b) monitor the working of the safeguards provided in the Constitution and in laws enacted by`
  line `Parliament and the State Legislatures;`
  line
  line `(c) make recommendations for the effective implementation of safeguards for the protection of`
  line `the interests of minorities by the Central Government or the State Governments;`
  line
  line `(d) look into specific complaints regarding deprivation of rights and safeguards of the minorities`
  line `and take up such matters with the appropriate authorities;`
  line
  line `(e) cause studies to be undertaken into problems arising out of any discrimination against`
  line `minorities and recommend measures for their removal;`
  line
  line `(f) conduct studies, research and analysis on the issues relating to socio-economic and educational`
  line `development of minorities;`
  line
  line `(g) suggest appropriate measures in respect of any minority to be undertaken by the Central`
  line `Government or the State Governments;`
  line
  line `(h) make periodical or special reports to the Central Government on any matter pertaining to`
  line `minorities and in particular difficulties confronted by them; and`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which may be referred to it by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall cause the recommendations referred to in clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) to be laid before each House of Parliament along with a memorandum explaining the`
  line `action taken or proposed to be taken on the recommendations relating to the Union and the reasons for the`
  line `non-acceptance, if any, of any of such recommendations.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any recommendation referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (1) or any part thereof with`
  line `which any State Government is concerned, the Commission shall forward a copy of such recommendation`
  line `or part to such State Government who shall cause it to be laid before the Legislature of the State along`
  line `with a memorandum explaining the action taken or proposed to be taken on the recommendations relating`
  line `to the State and the reasons for the non-acceptance, if any, of any of such recommendation or part.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commission shall, while performing any of the functions mentioned in sub-clauses (a), (b)`
  line `and (d) of sub-section (1), have all the powers of a civil court trying a suit and in particular, in respect of`
  line `the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person from any part of India and examining`
  line `him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses and documents; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (24670)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Grants by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24670&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Commission by way of grants such`
  line `sums of money as the Central Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission may spend such sums as it thinks fit for performing the functions under this Act,`
  line `and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the grants referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (24671)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Accounts and audit`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24671&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General at such`
  line `intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit shall be`
  line `payable by the Commission to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General and any person appointed by him in connection with the`
  line `audit of the accounts of the Commission under this Act shall have the same rights and privileges and the`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the`
  line `production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of`
  line `the offices of the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (24672)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24672&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall prepare, in such form and at such time, for each`
  line `financial year, as may be prescribed, its annual report, giving a full account of its activities during the`
  line `previous financial year and forward a copy thereof to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (24673)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Annual report and audit report to be laid before Parliament`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24673&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall`
  line `cause the annual report together with a memorandum of action taken on the recommendations contained`
  line `therein, in so far as they relate to the Central Government, and the reasons for the non-acceptance, if any,`
  line `of any of such recommendations and the audit report to be laid as soon as may be after the reports are`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (24674)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Chairperson, Members and staff of the Commission to be public servants`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24674&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson,`
  line `Members and employees of the Commission shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of`
  line `section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (24675)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24675&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `Chairperson and Members under sub-section (5) of section 4 and of officers and other employees`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section5;`
  line
  line `(b) any other matter under clause (f) of sub-section (4) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(c) the form in which the annual statement of accounts shall be maintained under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 11;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in, and the time at, which the annual report shall be prepared under section 12;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (24676)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944&sectionId=24676&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_41_69_00001_199219_1517807322944
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
